</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_EA.SGM_UCPN.EA.50395-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,395.10] Defined terms">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [50,395.10] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1995-25" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Evidence Act 1995</remotelink> cl 5.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.50395-10" type="ext"/>[50,395.10] </edpnum><title>Defined terms</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The term &#x201c;document&#x201d; is defined in the Dictionary. The circumstances in which documents are to be taken as &quot;available&quot; to parties are set out in 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.DICT1.DPT2.CL5" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">cl 5</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of Pt 2 of the Dictionary.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_EA.SGM_UCPN.EA.50395-15" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,395.15] Copy documents">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [50,395.15] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1898-11" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Evidence Act 1898</remotelink> s 34.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.50395-15" type="ext"/>[50,395.15] </edpnum><title>Copy documents</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>There have been long standing provisions allowing the tender of machine copies of documents: eg, Evidence Act 1898 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.EAN.S34" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">s 34</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
. Those provisions required the court to be satisfied that the copy had been made from the original, but expressly dispensed with any requirement that the copy had been compared with the original: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1894"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000325" spanref="cr000325-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WNNSW"/><ci:volume num="10"/><ci:page num="146"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Fanning v Griffiths</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000325-001" status="unval">(1894) 10 WN (NSW) 146</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. The present section, having regard to the court's power to admit documents that purport to be copies of an original, is consistent with the previous statutory provisions.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_EA.SGM_UCPN.EA.50395-20" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,395.20] Secondary evidence"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.50395-20" type="ext"/>[50,395.20] </edpnum><title>Secondary evidence</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Under the common law, the &#x201c;best evidence rule&#x201d; restricted the circumstances in which secondary evidence could be given of the contents of a document: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1962"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000326" spanref="cr000326-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="106"/><ci:page num="535"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000327" spanref="cr000327-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1962"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="406"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000328" spanref="cr000328-003" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ALJR"/><ci:volume num="35"/><ci:page num="416"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000329" spanref="cr000329-004"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC6200060"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Commissioner for Railways (NSW) v Young</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000326-001" status="unval">(1962) 106 CLR 535</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000327-002" status="unval">[1962] ALR 406</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000328-003" status="unval">(1962) 35 ALJR 416</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000329-004"> BC6200060</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="12412" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; see also <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1820"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000330" spanref="cr000330-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="B&amp;Ald"/><ci:volume num="3"/><ci:page num="566"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000331" spanref="cr000331-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ER"/><ci:volume num="106"/><ci:page num="768"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">R v Hunt</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000330-001" status="unval">(1820) 3 B &amp; Ald 566</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000331-002" status="unval">106 ER 768</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. However, the failure of a party to produce a document allowed the opposing party to give secondary evidence of its contents: see 
<remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.50395-20" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">[50,275.10]</remotelink>
. The present section adopts substantially the same approach by allowing a party to give secondary evidence of the contents of documents that are not available to the party: see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000332" spanref="cr000332-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="NSWIRComm"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="2003"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="148"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Campbell v Hitchcock</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000332-001" status="unval">[2003] NSWIRComm 148</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="389539" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000333" spanref="cr000333-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200406795"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Roads and Traffic Authority of NSW v Tetley</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2004] NSWSC 925; <ci:span spanid="cr000333-001" status="unval"> BC200406795</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="387652" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_EA.SGM_UCPN.EA.50395-25" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,395.25] Authenticity of documents"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.50395-25" type="ext"/>[50,395.25] </edpnum><title>Authenticity of documents</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>This section does not dispense with the need to establish the authenticity of documents, for example, where the relevance of a document depends on its authenticity as a record of business. Depending on the circumstances, it may be that neither the form nor the content of the document, nor even its production under subpoena, provide a sufficient basis for determining the authenticity of the document: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000334" spanref="cr000334-001" status="unval"><ci:volume num=""/><ci:page num=""/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000335" spanref="cr000335-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9902958"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">National Australia Bank Ltd v Rusu</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000334-001" status="unval">(1999) 47 NSWLR 309</ci:span> esp at 314&#x2013;315; [1999] NSWSC 539; <ci:span spanid="cr000335-002"> BC9902958</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="298509" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. In the case of a transcript of a tape recording, no oral or other evidence is required in order to authenticate the document, it is sufficient if it purports to be a transcript of the words spoken: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2002"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000336" spanref="cr000336-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ACrimR"/><ci:volume num="140"/><ci:page num="1"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000337" spanref="cr000337-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200204619"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">R v Giovannone</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000336-001" status="unval">(2002) 140 A Crim R 1</ci:span>; [2002] NSWCCA 323; <ci:span spanid="cr000337-002"> BC200204619</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="350623" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000338" spanref="cr000338-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9902633"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">R v Cassar</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [1999] NSWSC 436; <ci:span spanid="cr000338-001"> BC9902633</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="296677" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. The fact that a document may be a &#x201c;copy of a copy&#x201d; does not prevent it from being a &#x201c;copy&#x201d; within the meaning of s 48(4): see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000339" spanref="cr000339-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200205032"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Lewis v Nortex Pty Ltd (in liq)</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2002] NSWSC 337; <ci:span spanid="cr000339-001"> BC200205032</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="351287" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,400] s 49 Documents in foreign countries">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49" type="ext"/>[50,400]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Documents in foreign countries</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>49<fnr fnrtoken="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49.FT1-R" fntoken="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49.FT1">*</fnr></designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>No paragraph of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S48.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">section 48(1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 (other than 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S48.1.A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">paragraph (a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
) applies to a document that is in a foreign country unless:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49..A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49..A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the party who adduces evidence of the contents of the document in question has, not less than 28 days (or such other period as may be prescribed by the regulations or by rules of court) before the day on which the evidence is adduced, served on each other party a copy of the document proposed to be tendered, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49..B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49..B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>the court directs that it is to apply.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<glp:note>
<heading><title>Note:</title></heading>
<p>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="007S" refpt="COE.CML.EA95.S182" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Section 182</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Commonwealth Act gives 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="007S" refpt="COE.CML.EA95.S49" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">section 49</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Commonwealth Act a wider application in relation to Commonwealth records and certain Commonwealth documents.</text></p></glp:note><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[s 49  am Act No 53 of 2000  Sch 1]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,405] s 50 Proof of voluminous or complex documents">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50" type="ext"/>[50,405]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Proof of voluminous or complex documents</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>50</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The court may, on the application of a party, direct that the party may adduce evidence of the contents of 2 or more documents in question in the form of a summary if the court is satisfied that it would not otherwise be possible conveniently to examine the evidence because of the volume or complexity of the documents in question.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (1)  subst Act No 46 of 2007  s 3 and Sch 1[13], effective 1 January 2009]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2" type="ext"/>(2)<fnr fnrtoken="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.FT2-R" fntoken="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.FT2">**</fnr></designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The court may only make such a direction if the party seeking to adduce the evidence in the form of a summary has:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>served on each other party a copy of the summary that discloses the name and address of the person who prepared the summary, and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>given each other party a reasonable opportunity to examine or copy the documents in question.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The opinion rule does not apply to evidence adduced in accordance with a direction under this section.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<footnotegrp><footnote fnrtokens="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49.FT1-R" fntoken="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49.FT1" type="default"><fnlabel>*</fnlabel><fnbody>
<h>Editor's note:</h>
<p><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49.FT1" type="ext"/>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S49..A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Sections 49(a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 is a notification provision for the purposes of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.SCH2.PT2.CL3.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Sch 2 Pt 2 cl 3(1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Evidence Act 1995, reproduced at 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.SCH2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">[51,865]</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p></fnbody></footnote>
<footnote fnrtokens="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.FT2-R" fntoken="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.FT2" type="default"><fnlabel>**</fnlabel><fnbody>
<h>Editor's note:</h>
<p><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.FT2" type="ext"/>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S50.2.A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Section 50(2)(a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 is a notification provision for the purposes of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.SCH2.PT2.CL4" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Sch 2 Pt 2 cl 4</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Evidence Act 1995, reproduced at 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.EA.EAN95.SCH2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">[51,865]</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p></fnbody></footnote></footnotegrp>
</bodytext>
<level id="UCPN_EA.SGM_UCPN.EA.50405-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,405.5] Voluminous or complex documents"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.50405-5" type="ext"/>[50,405.5] </edpnum><title>Voluminous or complex documents</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The section makes no provision for the time when an application must be made. Importantly, it does not require that such application can only be made <emph typestyle="it">before</emph> the commencement of the hearing.</text></p>
<p>
<text>It has been observed in the context of a similar provision in Victoria that the construction of s 50 should be approached on the basis that it should not be given a restrictive or narrow interpretation: see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2011"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000340" spanref="cr000340-001"><ci:reporter value="ACSR"/><ci:volume num="85"/><ci:page num="144"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000341" spanref="cr000341-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC201106038"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Thackray v Gunns Plantations Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000340-001">(2011) 85 ACSR 144</ci:span>; [2011] VSC 380; <ci:span spanid="cr000341-002"> BC201106038</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="537577" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; see also <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000342" spanref="cr000342-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC201203607"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">In the matter of Idylic Solutions Pty Ltd; Australian Securities and Investments Commission v Hobbs</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2012] NSWSC 568; <ci:span spanid="cr000342-001" status="unval"> BC201203607</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="553502" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> and the authorities cited therein <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000343" spanref="cr000343-000" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="2012"/></ci:edition><ci:pinpoint num="19" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000343-000" status="unval">at [19]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S51"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,410] s 51 Original document rule abolished">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S51" type="ext"/>[50,410]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Original document rule abolished</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>51</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The principles and rules of the common law that relate to the means of proving the contents of documents are abolished.</text></p>
<glp:note>
<heading><title>Note:</title></heading>
<p>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.EA95.S182" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Section 182</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Commonwealth Act gives the provisions of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.EA95.PT2.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Part 2.2</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Commonwealth Act a wider application in relation to Commonwealth records and certain Commonwealth documents.</text></p></glp:note><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[s 51  am Act No 53 of 2000  Sch 1]</text></p></leg:histnote>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.EA.EAN95.S51.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_EA.SGM_UCPN.EA.50410-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[50,410.5]"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.EA.50410-5" type="ext"/>[50,410.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The abolition, by s 51, of the common law rules as to proof of the contents of documents does not abolish, or in any way affect, the need to prove in a particular case that a document which is tendered is, in fact, the document it purports to be: see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1999"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000344" spanref="cr000344-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="47"/><ci:page num="309"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000344" spanref="cr000344-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="314" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000345" spanref="cr000345-003"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9902958"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">National Australia Bank v Rusu</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000344-001">(1999) 47 NSWLR 309</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000344-002" status="unval">at 314</ci:span>; [1999] NSWSC 539; <ci:span spanid="cr000345-003"> BC9902958</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="298509" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:body></LEGDOC>